The**Waiting on Stock**trigger initiates a flow when a customer signs up to be notified about a product that is currently out of stock.**Note:**This Trigger is a part of [BigCommerce](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/6774740880153-Introduction-and-Installation-of-BigCommerce) Integration**Topics Covered:**[How to Configure Waiting on Stock Trigger](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780294519449-Waiting-on-Stock#h_01J8HEGN14MZE84RJD9WXXS6MK)[Practical Example](https://support.salesmate.io/hc/en-us/articles/37780294519449-Waiting-on-Stock#h_01J8HFBRR8269EVSRF1B9M4MG9)

### How to Configure Waiting on Stock Trigger

While creating the Trigger Based Flows select**Waiting on Stock**trigger

![mceclip0.png](./images/mceclip0-28.png)

When setting up the**Waiting on Stock**trigger, you need to configure the following elements:**Name:**Give the trigger a specific and meaningful name.**Description:**Write a brief summary that explains what the trigger does.**Select Store:**Choose the relevant BigCommerce Store that manages the product inventory.**Contact:**Indicate any specific criteria related to customer details or preferences.**BigCommerce:**Specify particular conditions related to the product.Once the configuration is completed, hit**Save**.

![mceclip1.png](./images/mceclip1-33.png)
